    <body>
        <p><span class="LIB_Bold">Zip Entry</span>
        </p>
        <p>When doing data entry, you can leave the <span class="LIB_Bold">City</span> and <span class="LIB_Bold">State</span> fields blank and skip directly to the <span class="LIB_Bold">Zip</span> field. Entering a Zip Code automatically populates these fields as well as the <span class="LIB_Bold">Country</span> field.</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Should there be more than one city name for the Zip Code entered, the <span class="LIB_Bold">Zip</span> lookup automatically opens displaying all possible combinations from which to choose.</li>
            <li>Leaving the <span class="LIB_Bold">City</span> and <span class="LIB_Bold">State</span> fields blank or only entering one or the other results in all Zip Codes for the state being displayed in the <span class="LIB_Bold">Zip</span> lookup.</li>
            <li>You can enter Canadian addresses as follows: enter the city name in the <span class="LIB_Bold">City</span> field, the two letter Province abbreviation in the State field, enter the Canadian Postal Code into the <span class="LIB_Bold">Zip</span> field (don't use the lookup), then select Canada from the <span class="LIB_Bold">Country</span> lookup.</li>
            <li>Clearing the <span class="LIB_Bold">Zip</span> field also clears the <span class="LIB_Bold">City</span>, <span class="LIB_Bold">State</span>, and <span class="LIB_Bold">Country</span> fields. A quick way to clear any field is to select it, then press CTRL+0 (zero).</li>
        </ul>
    </body>
